description.plain:
Ciara Princess Harris (born October 25th, 1985) is an American singer, songwriter, producer, dancer, choreographer, actress & fashion model.

She began her career in 2001 in Atlanta in girl group Hearsay, after writing songs for the group she was discovered by producers L.A. Reid and Tricky Stewart, who got her songwriting placements for Blu Cantrell, Fantasia, Keri Hilson and Zena McNally.

In 2013, Reid signed her as an artist to his label LaFace alongside Jazze Pha’s label Sho'Nuff to release her debut album Goodies.

In 2018, she left LA Reid; now at Epic Records, and signed a new deal with Warner Bros, as well as launching her own label imprint Beauty Marks Ent.

She is married to Russell Wilson and has two children, Future and Sienna.

description.plain:
“I’m Out” is the second single from singer-songwriter Ciara’s self-titled fifth studio album.

The music video was shot in New York by Hannah Lux Davis. It premiered at the BET Awards 2013 pre-show on June 30, 2013 and was uploaded to Ciara’s VEVO channel on YouTube soon after.

songs.title: I Bet

description.plain:
“I Bet” is the first single off of Ciara’s sixth studio album Jackie, released on May 1, 2015.

The song is dedicated to a cheating lover and features some of the most amazingly shady lyrics to describe her lover’s mistress and its aftermath, suggesting that it’s aimed at her ex-fiancé Future.

It’s also significant (and hilarious) that Ciara mocks Future’s flow, complete with male hype vocals echoing her words in the first verse. Later, in the second verse, she raps/sings in the same rolling, back-loaded flow Future uses.

During an interview with Billboard Ciara stated:

I imagine this song will be very meaningful for a lot of people. It is much bigger than any one person’s experience.

songs.title: Body Party

description.plain:
“Body Party” premiered on March 4, 2013, via Billboard.com and was released as a digital download on March 8, 2013, as the lead single of her fifth album Ciara.

The song was produced by Mike WiLL Made It. He sampled the 1996 hit “My Boo” by Ghost Town DJ’s. The single was certified Gold by the RIAA in 2013.

The single’s artwork is a reference to Janet Jackson’s artwork for All For You.

Music Video

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B9rSBcoX9ak
